'''Jim Bruene''' is a financial [[journalist]] .
==Early life and education== Bruene graduated the [[University of Washington]] with an [[MBA]] in Marketing and Finance and [[Iowa State University]] with a [[Bachelor of Science|BS]] in [[Engineering]].{{Citation needed|date=September 2015}}
==Career== In 1994, Bruene founded Financial Innovations{{clarify|date=September 2015}} and Digital Banking Report{{clarify|date=September 2015}} (that was called Online Banking Report when it was established in 1995). He set up Tracking fintech & financial services innovations.<ref name="BankNXTonBruene">{{cite web|url=http://banknxt.com/author/jim-bruene/|title= Author - Jim Bruene |last=|first=|work=|publisher=BankNXT|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref> He is the organizer and writer for the Online Banking Report.
He is the founder of the Finovate conference series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/tech/s/5-ways-to-yourself-using-mobile-payment-apps-like-venmo-185310508.html|title=5 ways to protect yourself while using mobile payment apps like Venmo|date=6 March 2015|work=[[Yahoo!]]|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref>
Bruene spent two years as a deposit and [[credit card]] [[product manager]] for [[First Interstate Bancorp|First Interstate Bank]] between 1988 and 1990. He then became a Loan and Mortgage Product Manager for [[Security Pacific Bank]] until 1992. At that point he spent a further two years at [[US Bancorp]] in the area of online banking product development, specifically with [[Microsoft Money]].<ref name="LinkedIn">{{cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/bruene|title=Jim Bruene Owner, The Finovate Group|last=|first=|work=[[LinkedIn]]|publisher=LinkedIn|accessdate=17 September 2015}} {{unreliable source?|date=September 2015}}</ref> He also worked for [[Caterpillar Inc.]], and in an advisory capacity for [[X.com]]/[[PayPal]] and ING Direct among others.
===Finance industry=== In 1994 Bruene founded Online Financial Innovations. Since then he has worked as its publisher, been the editor and is in charge of leading content of newsletters and reports on retail financial services (including: [[electronic billing]], payments, e-messaging, statements, small business banking, online loan origins, etc.), working with financial institutions offering strategy advice for enhancing online services and [[Return on Investment]] (ROI).<ref name="OBR">{{cite web|url=http://www.onlinebankingreport.com/a_dev/Bruene2004.pdf|title=Bruene 2004|last=|first=|work=|publisher=Online Banking Report|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref>
===Financial journals=== Bruene has a presence in the world of financial journals. He is often quoted in [[American Banker]], [[CNNfn]], [[Forbes]], [[Money Magazine]], [[MSNBC]], [[The New York Times]], PC Week, [[SmartMoney]], [[The Financial Times]], [[The Wall Street Journal]], and [[The Washington Post]].<ref name="About Jim Bruene">{{cite web|url=http://www.onlinebankingreport.com/about/|title=About Our Company|last=|first=|work=|publisher=Online Banking Report|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref>
He has spoken at a variety of forums in the finance sector such as: ABA Annual Convention, BAI's Retail Delivery, and CBA Executive Convention.<ref name="DBR">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=27274848&privcapId=26763499|title=Executive Profile Jim Bruene |last=|first=|work=|publisher=Bloomberg|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref>
